  "fileData": null,
  "description": "This part replaces a Zome ball where you need to have two blue lines intersecting, lying in the red plane, at an angle of 72 degrees. &nbsp;Its purpose is aesthetic, when you don&#39;t want to use a ball to make the junction. &nbsp;This might happen if you&#39;re trying to represent a mathematical object wherein balls should represent vertices, not false vertices arising from edge intersections.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSix copies are modeled as a single print, with small sprues connecting the individual bobs. &nbsp;They can be twisted apart, then cleaned up with a sharp knife or nail clippers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;",
